    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="55"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">110.11 DU/9–1554</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Prime
                        Minister <persName corresp="#p_MENDESFP1" type="to">Mendès-France</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d55fn1">The source text, drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName>, was transmitted to the
                        Embassy in Paris in <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> telegram 954 of
                        Sept. 15 with instructions that it be delivered to <persName
                            corresp="#p_MENDESFP1">Mendès-France</persName> as a personal
                        message.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-15">September 15,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: This is just a brief note to
                    let you know that I plan to make a quick visit to London and Bonn Thursday and
                        <pb facs="0128" n="1196" xml:id="pg_1196"/> Friday. I regret that time is so
                    short because it will not permit me to stop over in Paris to talk with you much
                    as I would like to do so. However I hope that we will have this opportunity very
                    shortly when we meet either in London or in New York at the <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Until then, with best wishes,<note n="2" xml:id="d55fn2">In telegram 1098 from
                        Paris, Sept. 15, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DILLONCD1"
                            >Dillon</persName> informed the Department of State that the message was
                        delivered and that the effect of omitting Paris from the Secretary’s
                        itinerary “will be salutatory” (110.11 DU/9–1554).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foster Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
